com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.software.reports

Interface LastCheckResult

  • All Superinterfaces:
    LastCheckResultTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LastCheckResultStub

    public interface LastCheckResult
extends Service, LastCheckResultTypes
    The LastCheckResult interface provides methods to get the most recent available result of the checks that have been run on a cluster before the application of the desired software document to all hosts within the cluster.

        Returns the most recent available result of checks run on the cluster before the application of the desired software document to all hosts within the cluster.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The cluster identifier. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        Returns:
        Most recent result available of the checks run on the cluster.
        Throws:
        Error - If there is an unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        NotFound - If there is no cluster associated with cluster in the system or if there is no result associated with the cluster cluster
